                            <comment id="13536323" author="jcoveney" created="Wed, 19 Dec 2012 19:10:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A minor nit, but since you add the new constructor, you can just do the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; JsonMetadata() {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;.pig_schema&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;.pig_header&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;.pig_stats&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The advantage being that if we change the logic around what to do with those file names, it can be kept in one place.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
